modules.description: This module provides parallelized versions of common list and array operations, including mapping, iterating, and folding, with optional initialization, finalization, and execution control. It supports list and array data structures, preserving input order for mapping operations. Concrete use cases include accelerating data processing tasks like batch computation, parallel filtering, and distributed transformations across multiple cores.

This module enables parallel execution of computation-intensive tasks across multiple cores, coordinating input distribution, processing, and result aggregation. It works with arbitrary data types via user-defined `demux`, `work`, and `mux` functions, supporting chunked processing and ordered or unordered result accumulation. Concrete use cases include parallel parsing of input streams, distributed image processing, and batch machine learning inference with custom initialization and cleanup per worker.
